{[#]Black's minor pieces are stuck while White has made important kingside
progress.} 20... Rf4 {This looks more like a desperate move.} 21. Rhg1 $1 {
White simply ignores the rook.} ({If} 21. Bxf4 $2 exf4 {the g5-pawn is hanging
while the g7-bishop is really dangerous. If} 22. Rhg1 $2 Nca4 $1 {Black wins
quickly.}) 21... Qf8 ({It is a pity that the thematic} 21... Nxe4 22. Ndxe4
Rxe4 {backfires to} 23. Qxe4 $1 Bf5 24. Bg4 Bxe4+ 25. Nxe4 Rxc1+ 26. Rxc1 $18 {
Black is helpless against the threat 27.Bxb6 Qxb6 28.Be6+ Kf8 29.Nf6 Bxf6 30.
gxf6 setting up a mating network. White has an even more sadistic plan
consisting of 27.Bd2 followed by Ba5, paralyzing Black completely.}) 22. f3 Be8
23. Qd1 {White simply intends to start his attack along the h-file.} h5 24.
gxh6 Bxh6 25. Rh1 Rh4 26. Rxh4 Bxe3 {Black has managed to exchange his rook
for the dark-squared bishop but his structure remains worse and his king
vulnerable.} 27. Rc2 Qf6 28. Rh1 Qg5 29. Nc4 $18 {and White won.} 1-0

