{We will now investigate some possible effects of ...f7-f5 which we did not
mention above.[#]Black's last move has been the apparently strategically
consistent 16...f5. Paradoxically, this allows White to start a decisive
attack by two apparent positional concessions.} 17. hxg6 $1 hxg6 18. exf5 $1
gxf5 19. Bh5 Re7 20. Bg6 Nf8 21. Qh5 Nxg6 22. Qxg6 Nd3 23. Nde4 ({and now the
simplest win would have been} 23. Qh7+ Kf7 24. Rh6 Kf8 25. Qh8+ Bxh8 26. Rxh8+
Kg7 27. Rxd8 $18) 1-0

