{[#]The central knight is hanging and White threatens to start an attack along
the g-file. Can Black maintain approximate equality?} 19... d5 $1 {This strong
move consolidates the knight taking advantage of the fact that after the
opening of the c-file the white king would be vulnerable.} (19... Qe7 $6 {
This natural move offers White an essential tempo for starting his attack.} 20.
Rhg1 Kh8 21. g5 hxg5 22. Nxg5 Nf6 23. f4 $16) (19... f4 $2 {weakens the light
squares too much.} 20. Qxe4 fxe3 21. Rxd6 $18 {[%cal Ge2d3] followed by Bd3
with a decisive attack.}) 20. Nh4 $2 {This should have led to problems, but
White is not better at all in any case.} (20. cxd5 $2 cxd5 21. Rxd5 Be6 $17 {
[%cal Ga8c8] threatening ...Rc8.}) (20. gxf5 {This is relatively best but does
not shake Black's stability.} Bxf5 21. Nh4 (21. Bd3 Nd6) 21... Bh7 {with
comfortable black play.}) 20... f4 $1 $17 {Black avoids the opening of the
g-file and gains more space in the centre.} (20... d4 {was milder:} 21. gxf5
Nc5 22. Rhg1 dxe3 23. Rxg7+ Kxg7 24. Rg1+ Kf6 $11 {Ni,H (2704)-Ding,L (2755)
China 2015 (0-1, 37)}) *

