} Bf5 22. gxf6 Nxf6 23. Qd1 Ng4 24. Bxc5 Rxc5 25. e6 Ne3 26. Qd2 Nxc4 $19)
21... Rxc5 22. e5 $1 {Now that Black does not control d3 anymore, this is
well-timed.} fxg5 (22... Bf5 {is parried with} 23. gxf6 (23. Bd3 fxg5 $1) 23...
Nxf6 24. Bd3 $11) 23. Qxg6 Bf5 $2 {Probably dicated by premature panicking.
Black gives up the d6-pawn for nothing.} ({Black should have taken the
exchange as White's attack along the b1-h7 diagonal offers him only equal play.
} 23... Bxf1 24. Rxf1 g4 25. Bd3 Rxf3 26. Qxh7+ Kf8 27. Rxf3+ gxf3 28. Qf5+ Qf7
$5 29. Qxf7+ Kxf7 30. Ne4 Bxe5 $11) 24. Qxd6 Qxd6 25. exd6 g4 26. Nd2 $16 {
Anton Guijarro,D (2666) -Demchenko,A (2660) Riadh 2017 (½-½, 68)} *

