{[#]Black is in trouble, but he can still avoid immediate disaster. How?} 22...
Rcd8 $5 {One of the two reasonable moves, defending d7.} (22... cxd5 $5 {
is also playable, as it clears the c-file for the rook.} 23. Nxc5 Rxc5 24. Rxd5
({The point is that without a hanging rook on c8,} 24. Qd7+ Re7 25. Qd8 Re8 {
leads nowhere.}) 24... Rxd5 25. cxd5 a4) (22... Rc7 $2 {This loses to} 23. Nxc5
dxc5 24. d6 $18 {[%cal Gh3d7] followed by Qd7+.}) (22... Qxc4 $2 {This is the
game continuation.} 23. Nxc5 Qxc5 24. Qd7+ Kg8 {Matlakov,M (2665)-Gladyszev,O 
(2446) St Petersburg 2012 (1-0, 25) You are invited to deliver the decisive
blow in the next test.}) (22... Nxb3) 23. Nxc5 dxc5 {Black is clearly
struggling strategically but not everything is lost yet.} *

