{[#]White to move and win.} 20. e5 $1 {This thematic break is especially
effective with the c5-pawn and the d6-square insufficiently well defended.}
Nxe5 (20... dxe5 {leads to similar play.} 21. d6 Qd8 22. Nd5 $18 {Black has
worries on both wings. The pawn on c5 is hanging and the threat Qh6 followed
by Ne7+ is crushing.}) (20... fxe5 {opens the f-file for White's attack.} 21.
Ng5 $18 {With the rook isolated on a7 Black cannot stand the attack.}) 21. bxc5
Nxf3+ 22. Rxf3 dxc5 23. d6 Qd8 24. Nd5 $18 {Black cannot survive the combined
attack of all of White's pieces.} *

